trend_summary: Industrial clusters expand westward, while scattered infill housing and several commercial redevelopments fill vacant lots. A highway interchange is upgraded and parking areas enlarge, yet small parks and street-tree plantings slightly boost overall greenery. Change is incremental, keeping a mid-level, car-oriented suburban form with no large high-rise growth.
notable_changes: New and enlarged warehouse roofs along the western rail / highway corridor.
Addition of exit ramps and realignment of lanes at the main interchange south-east of centre.
Conversion of a former industrial block near the centre into a big-box retail lot with large parking.
Resurfacing and expansion of a school sports field and adjacent parking on the east side.
Progressive increase of tree cover along residential streets and riverfront buffers.
